The assumption is reasonable, because when an inappropriate context provider gets the right to provide bad context, as a punishment, its  reputation will decrease, and the proceeds is also very small.
Since the negotiation takes place in pervasive  environments, time is a critical factors.
As context providers are independent, factors which influence their negotiation stance and behavior are  private and not available to their opponents.
After guaranteeing the  system"s interest, they can try to maximize their own  personal interests.
